(551, 23, 'What is Git?', 'A web hosting service for web developers', 'A distributed version control system to track changes in source code', 'A programming language used for scripting', 'A relational database management tool', 2, 1),
(552, 23, 'Who created the Git version control system?', 'Guido van Rossum', 'Linus Torvalds', 'Bill Gates', 'Ada Lovelace', 2, 1),
(553, 23, 'Which Git command is used to initialize a new, empty Git repository in your current directory?', 'git start', 'git create', 'git init', 'git new', 3, 1),
(554, 23, 'Which command shows the current state of the working directory and the staging area?', 'git show', 'git status', 'git log', 'git diff', 2, 1),
(555, 23, 'How do you stage a specific file named ''index.html'' to prepare it for committing?', 'git add index.html', 'git stage index.html', 'git commit index.html', 'git push index.html', 1, 1),
(556, 23, 'What is the correct command to record staged changes (a commit) with a descriptive message?', 'git commit ''Message''', 'git commit -m \"Message\"', 'git save -m \"Message\"', 'git record \"Message\"', 2, 1),
(557, 23, 'What is the purpose of the ''git clone'' command?', 'To make an exact duplicate of a file in the working directory', 'To copy an existing Git repository from a remote source to your local machine', 'To create a copy of a branch locally', 'To upload local files to the remote master branch', 2, 1),
(558, 23, 'Which command displays the chronological history of commits in the current repository?', 'git history', 'git show', 'git log', 'git status', 3, 1),
(559, 23, 'What is a branch in Git?', 'A copy of the repository kept on another computer', 'An independent line of development, represented by a movable pointer to a commit', 'A special tag used to mark a software release', 'A directory within the repository structure', 2, 1),
(560, 23, 'Which command creates a new branch named ''feature-xyz'' and switches to it immediately?', 'git branch -c feature-xyz', 'git checkout -b feature-xyz', 'git switch -n feature-xyz', 'git merge feature-xyz', 2, 1),
(561, 23, 'How do you merge a branch named ''feature-login'' into your currently active branch?', 'git join feature-login', 'git merge feature-login', 'git combine feature-login', 'git pull feature-login', 2, 1),
(562, 23, 'What does the ''git push'' command do?', 'Downloads changes from a remote repository', 'Uploads local repository commits to a remote repository', 'Moves files from the working directory to the staging area', 'Applies local stashed changes back to the working directory', 2, 1),
(563, 23, 'What does the ''git pull'' command do?', 'Fetches changes from a remote repository and immediately merges them into the current active branch', 'Pushes local commits to the remote repository', 'Deletes the remote repository tracking branch', 'Resets the working directory to the last commit state', 1, 1),
(564, 23, 'What is the key difference between ''git fetch'' and ''git pull''?', 'git fetch merges changes automatically, while git pull does not', 'git fetch only downloads remote tracking changes without modifying your local working files, while git pull downloads and merges them', 'git fetch is used for remote repositories, while git pull is only for local ones', 'There is no difference; they are exact aliases of each other', 2, 1),
(565, 23, 'What is the purpose of ''git stash''?', 'To delete unneeded commits from the repository history', 'To permanently save work to the remote repository', 'To temporarily save (shelve) changes in your working directory so you can work on something else, then restore them later', 'To password-protect sensitive files in your project', 3, 1),
(566, 23, 'Which command is used to list all remote repositories along with their fetch and push URLs?', 'git remote', 'git remote -v', 'git show remotes', 'git url -list', 2, 1),
(567, 23, 'What is a Pull Request (PR) on GitHub?', 'A command line request to download a branch', 'A feature that allows you to propose changes from your branch to another repository/branch and request review and merging', 'A request to pull files from a staging server to a production server', 'A notification that your repository has been successfully cloned by someone else', 2, 1),
(568, 23, 'What is the default primary branch name in modern Git and GitHub repositories?', 'master', 'main', 'primary', 'trunk', 2, 1),
(569, 23, 'Which command discards all local uncommitted changes in your working directory and resets it to the last commit?', 'git reset --hard', 'git clean -f', 'git checkout .', 'Both git reset --hard and git checkout . are correct methods depending on scope', 4, 1),
(570, 23, 'What is the purpose of a ''.gitignore'' file?', 'To list files that should be encrypted during git push', 'To specify intentional untracked files or directories that Git should ignore', 'To hide files from the local file explorer on your system', 'To prevent other developers from editing specific files in the repository', 2, 1),
(571, 23, 'Which command is used to show differences between the working directory and the staging area?', 'git status', 'git diff', 'git show', 'git compare', 2, 1),
(572, 23, 'Which command is used to delete a local branch named ''old-feature''?', 'git branch -d old-feature', 'git branch -delete old-feature', 'git remove branch old-feature', 'git checkout -delete old-feature', 1, 1),
(573, 23, 'What is git rebase?', 'A command to reset the entire git config back to factory defaults', 'The process of moving or combining a sequence of commits to a new base commit to maintain a clean linear history', 'A way to rename a remote repository URL', 'A security check to verify file integrity within a commit', 2, 1),
(574, 23, 'What does the ''HEAD'' pointer represent in a Git repository?', 'The first commit ever made in the repository', 'The main administrator of the repository', 'A reference to the currently active branch or commit you are working on', 'The remote server address', 3, 1),
(575, 23, 'What is a ''fork'' on GitHub?', 'A command to split a single file into two separate files', 'A personal copy of someone''s repository created on your own GitHub account to make changes independently', 'A plugin to speed up code compilation', 'A conflict that occurs when two people commit to the same line', 2, 1),

